    </div>
    <div class="sidebar-master-check checked" data-patch="sidebar-nav-privacy" data-section="privacy" data-master-for="adblock-toggle pause-site-btn ua-request ua-page custom-filters adblock-allowlist" onclick="toggleSidebarMaster(this)"></div>
  </div>
  <div class="settings-card">
    <div class="settings-card-head"><i class="fas fa-shield-halved"></i> Privacy &amp; Blocking</div>
    <div class="settings-card-body">
      <div class="patch-row"><div class="patch-row-info"><div class="patch-row-label">Ad &amp; Tracker Blocking toggle</div><div class="patch-row-desc"><strong>Uncheck to permanently disable</strong> ad/tracker blocking and remove its toggle from Settings and the toolbar. Cannot be re-enabled at runtime.</div></div><div class="patch-check checked" data-patch="adblock-toggle" data-section="privacy" onclick="togglePatch(this)"></div></div>
      <div class="patch-row"><div class="patch-row-info"><div class="patch-row-label">"Pause for this site" button</div><div class="patch-row-desc"><strong>Uncheck to remove</strong> the per-site pause button from the adblock toolbar popup. Users will only be able to globally disable ad blocking, not pause it per-site.</div></div><div class="patch-check checked" data-patch="pause-site-btn" data-section="privacy" onclick="togglePatch(this)"></div></div>
      <div class="patch-row"><div class="patch-row-info"><div class="patch-row-label">Paused sites allowlist</div><div class="patch-row-desc"><strong>Uncheck to remove</strong> the paused-sites textarea from Settings › Privacy. Sites cannot be individually allowlisted from the Settings page — only via the toolbar popup button (if kept above).</div></div><div class="patch-check checked" data-patch="adblock-allowlist" data-section="privacy" onclick="togglePatch(this)"></div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="settings-card">
